--------------------
DESCRIPTION
--------------------

a Symfony2 Bundle to handle file upload


--------------------
INSTALL
--------------------

# /deps
[wbxFileBundle]
    git=http://github.com/ma2thieu/wbxFileBundle.git
    target=bundles/wbx/FileBundle

# /app/AppKernel.php
$bundles = array(
	...
	new wbx\FileBundle\wbxFileBundle(),
	...

# app/autoload.php
$loader->registerNamespaces(array(
	...
    'wbx'               => __DIR__.'/../vendor/bundles',
	...


--------------------
EXEMPLE :
--------------------

>>> ENTITY :

/**
 * @var \wbx\FileBundle\Entity\File $image
 *
 * @ORM\ManyToOne(targetEntity="\wbx\FileBundle\Entity\File", cascade={"all"})
 * @ORM\JoinColumn(name="image_id", referencedColumnName="id")
 */
private $image;

/**
 * Set image
 *
 * @param \wbx\FileBundle\Entity\File $image
 */
public function setImage(\wbx\FileBundle\Entity\File $image) {
    $this->image = $image;
}

/**
 * Get image
 *
 * @return integer
 */
public function getImage() {
    return $this->image;
}


>>> FORM :

$builder
    ->add('image', new \wbx\FileBundle\Form\FileType())


>>> CONTROLLER :

nothing to do


>>> VIEW :

{% include 'wbxFileBundle:File:embed_one.html.twig' with {
    'form'              : edit_form.image,
    'imagine_filter'    : "my_thumb_filter"
} %}

'form' is mandatory
'imagine_filter' is optional : if set the bundle AvalancheImagineBundle (https://github.com/avalanche123/AvalancheImagineBundle) is needed and the value of imagine_filter will be used as a the name of the Imagine filter to be called to create and display a thumbnail of the picture.
If imagine_filter is not defined or == "" a link to the file will be displayed







